21/09/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The economy grew by 6 per cent in the second quarter of 2004, beating analysts' expectations that growth would match the first quarter's 5.3 per cent. The government had forecast economic growth of around 5 per cent for the year, a figure now viewed as conservative. 
In other news Monday (20 September), Bulgaria's Deputy Justice Minister Mario Dimitrov resigned over scandals related to international adoptions. Publications in the Bulgarian and Western press recently unveiled a number of channels for illegal "exports" of Bulgarian babies abroad. In most cases, Bulgarian Roma bore the children for money. (Trud - 21/09/04; UPI, bTV - 20/09/04) 
